        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Vancomycin intermittent infusion guidelines for adult patients 1  Introduction"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 3
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.1,
                "text": "This guidance covers the use of intravenous vancomycin prescribed as intermittent infusion in adult patients."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 4
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 1.2,
                "text": "For patients on continuous vancomycin infusion in the hospital, please refer to the local site guidance."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 5
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.3,
                "text": "The aim of therapy is to maintain an appropriate vancomycin level to ensure efficacy whilst minimising risk of nephrotoxicity and oto-toxicity."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 6
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.4,
                "text": "Vancomycin is a glycopeptide antibiotic which has bactericidal activity against aerobic and anaerobic Gram-positive bacteria including multi-resistant staphylococcus aureus (MRSA). However, there are reports of Staphylococcus aureus with reduced susceptibility to glycopeptides. There are increasing reports of Vancomycin resistant enterococci (VRE). Please review with microbiology consultant if a patient is known to be colonised with VRE"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 7
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "Scope"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 8
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.1,
                "text": "The guidelines aim to provide recommendations on dosing and monitoring of vancomycin levels in adult patients. It is for use by all healthcare professionals across MSE Foundation Trust."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 9
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.0,
                "text": "Dosing and administration"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 10
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.1,
                "text": "Reconstitution"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 11
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "At the time of use, add 10 ml of sterile Water for Injections to each 500 mg vial of Vancomycin Hydrochloride and 20ml to each 1g vial to give 50mg/ml solution."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 12
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Reconstituted solutions would require further dilution prior to administration; see Table 1 below: Vancomycin loading dose."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 13
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.2,
                "text": "Loading Dose"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 14
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "A loading dose of 25\u201330 mg/kg of body weight is used to facilitate rapid attainment of target trough serum concentration."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 15
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The initial loading dose should be based on total body weight."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 16
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Where the patient cannot be weighed, use estimated ideal body weight(IBW)"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Where the patient looks underweight, use estimated weight, do NOT use IBW"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "In the critically ill patient with renal insufficiency, the initial loading dose should NOT be reduced."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Loading dose does not take account of renal function; on rare occasions a patient's clearance of vancomycin may be so high that the maintenance dose is higher than the loading dose. In these circumstances, give the maintenance dose as a loading dose instead."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 3.3,
                "text": "Follow the recommendation in Table 1 for initial loading dose."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.4,
                "text": "Table1: Vancomycin LOADING dose"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "sequence_num": 23,
            "data": {
                "num_rows": 5,
                "num_cols": 4,
                "table_items": [
                    {
                        "text": "Actual Body Weight"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Dose"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Volume Sodium Chloride 0.9% OR Glucose 5% (\u2264 5mg/ml)"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Duration of Infusion"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "<40kg"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "750mg"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "250ml"
                    },
                    {
